## Migration to yba_backup_schedule

Replace `yba_backups` with `yba_backup_schedule` and update `keyspace` to `keyspaces` (list):

```hcl
# Before (deprecated)
resource "yba_backups" "example" {
  keyspace = "my_keyspace"
  # ...
}

# After
resource "yba_backup_schedule" "example" {
  keyspaces = ["my_keyspace"]  # Specific keyspace/database
  # ...
}

# Or for full universe backup (all keyspaces/databases):
resource "yba_backup_schedule" "full_backup" {
  keyspaces = []  # Empty list = full universe backup
  # ...
}
```

The HCL schema changed (`keyspace` -> `keyspaces`), so a `terraform state mv` does not work cleanly across the rename. Drop the old resource from state on v0.1.x, upgrade the provider, write the new `yba_backup_schedule` HCL, and re-import using the existing schedule UUID:

```sh
# On v0.1.x, before upgrading:
terraform state rm yba_backups.example

# After upgrading to v1.0.0:
terraform import yba_backup_schedule.example <schedule-uuid>
terraform plan
```

See the [Upgrading to v1.0.0](../guides/upgrading-to-v1.0.0) guide for the full workflow.

